s in which three fundamental philosophical, psychoanalytic, and literary texts can be reread in light of their confrontation with a seemingly inhuman force at the heart of the foundation of the human subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aEthics in literature. 0aEuropean literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEuropean literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMoral conditions in literature. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478094040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804780940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804780940.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles